well, there&#39;s this idea: http://json-schema.org/

right now, i use out-of-band documentation to let folks know what&#39;s allowed
in POST/PUT and what is returned in GET.

most of the time, JSON requests for services i create are negotiated via the
Accept header and that usually means folks can also negotiate some XML
flavor of the same representation in order to get an idea of what is
avail/expected in a form that may be a bit easier to grok/validate, etc.

